 x(y) = \int dx = - \int \frac{dy}{qy^4 + y} = -\frac13\int \frac{d(y^3)}{y^3(qy^3+1)} = -\frac13 \int \left(\frac{1}{y^3} - \frac{q}{qy^3+1}\right)d(y^3)\\ = -\frac13 \left(\log(y^3)-\log(qy^3+1)\right) + K = -\frac13 \log\left(\frac{-y^3}{qy^3+1}\right) + K' 
K' = 1-\frac13 \log(8 - q) \quad\implies\quad x = 1 -\frac13 \log\left(\frac{(8-q)(-y^3)}{1+qy^3}\right) 
\begin{align} \frac{-y^3}{1+qy^3} = \frac{1}{8-q}e^{3(1-x)} \iff & -y^3 = \frac{\frac{1}{8-q}e^{3(1-x)}}{1 + \frac{q}{8-q}e^{3(1-x)}} =\frac{1}{(8-q)e^{3(x-1)} + q }\\ \iff &   \quad y\,  = -\left((8-q)e^{3(x-1)} + q\right)^{-1/3}\\ \iff &   \quad y\,  = -\frac12 e^{1-x} \left(1- \frac{q}{8}( 1 - e^{3(1-x)})\right)^{-1/3} \end{align}
y = -\frac12 e^{1-x} \left( 1 + \frac{q}{24} ( 1 - e^{3(1-x)}) + O(q^2)\right)\tag{*1}
